				<div id="powerplay">
					<div class="list-group">

						<div class="list-group-item active">

							<h2 class="list-group-item-heading">Powerplay</h2>

						</div>

						<div class="list-group-item">

							<h2 class="list-group-item-heading">Umbrella Powerplay Options</h2>

							<p>All positions are pretty much interchangeable on the powerplay. Think of each color as spots, everyone should be able to play any spot.</p>

							<h4>Important Concepts</h4>

							<p>We are out numbering the defense high in the zone. Red, Teal and Blue have 2 defenders defending them. This is our point of puck control. In theory we should be able to hold the puck between the 3 of them for the entire powerplay if we chose not to shoot. We must know our options to relieve pressure for aggressive penalty killers. Do not panick, find the open man to relieve pressure.</p>

							<p>Yellow should postion himself medium to high in the slot. Do not get too close to the goalie where you are not a passing option. This will also give you a better angle for a potential one timer.</p>

							<tabset>

								<tab>

									<tab-heading>Slot One-T</tab-heading>

									<table class="table table-bordered no-top">
										<tbody>
											<tr>
